  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dc3 \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc5\u0db9 \u0d8b\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0\u0db8\u0db1\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0da7 54.6\u0d9a\u0dca \u0daf\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "June Colombo inflation up to 54.6 percent",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Surface inflation, measured by the annual point change in the Colombo Consumer Price Index, rose from 39.1% in May 2022 to 54.6% in June 2022.",
        "This rise in annual point inflation has been driven by monthly increases in the prices of items in both the food and non-food categories.",
        "Accordingly, the annual point inflation in the food category increased from 57.4 in May 2022 to 80.1% in June 2022, and the annual point inflation in the non-food category increased from 30.6% in May 2022 to 41.4% in June 2022."
      ],
